\subsection{Operational Notes}\label{operational-notes}

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  If you change the embedding dimension or metric, existing HNSW files
  must be rebuilt or carefully validated. Use metadata to detect
  mismatches at load time.
\item
  Ensure \texttt{auto\_sentence\_id} resumes from the highest SID on
  disk at load time to preserve global SID uniqueness.
\item
  When upgrading offset file format, implement a loader that detects old
  layout and upgrades to the new format (or reject old files
  explicitly).
\item
  Prefer export of indexes and offsets as separate artifacts to allow
  migration, offline repair, and cross-system portability.
\end{itemize}

\begin{center}\rule{0.5\linewidth}{0.5pt}\end{center}

